# Environment Variables

This file documents the environment variables required for the admin_side module.

## Required Environment Variables

### GraphQL API (my-cms backend)
```bash
# GraphQL API endpoint - https://github.com/doitsu2014/my-cms
PUBLIC_GRAPHQL_API_URL=http://localhost:4000/graphql
# GraphQL Cache API endpoint (optional)
PUBLIC_GRAPHQL_CACHE_API_URL=http://localhost:4000/graphql
```

### Keycloak Authentication (Phase 8)
```bash
# Keycloak server URL
PUBLIC_KEYCLOAK_URL=https://my-ids-admin.ducth.dev
# Keycloak realm name
PUBLIC_KEYCLOAK_REALM=my-realm
# Keycloak client ID for admin_side
PUBLIC_KEYCLOAK_CLIENT_ID=admin-side-client
```

### Upload/Storage (Optional)
```bash
# Media upload endpoint
PUBLIC_MEDIA_UPLOAD_API_URL=http://localhost:4000/api/media/upload
```

### Cache Configuration (Optional)
```bash
# Enable homepage cache (optional)
HOME_PAGE_CACHE_ENABLED=false
```

## Development Setup

1. Copy this file to `.env.local` in the admin_side directory
2. Update the values according to your environment
3. Never commit `.env.local` to version control

## Example .env.local

```bash
# Backend API
PUBLIC_GRAPHQL_API_URL=http://localhost:4000/graphql
PUBLIC_GRAPHQL_CACHE_API_URL=http://localhost:4000/graphql
PUBLIC_MEDIA_UPLOAD_API_URL=http://localhost:4000/api/media/upload

# Keycloak
PUBLIC_KEYCLOAK_URL=https://my-ids-admin.ducth.dev
PUBLIC_KEYCLOAK_REALM=production
PUBLIC_KEYCLOAK_CLIENT_ID=admin-side-client

# Optional
HOME_PAGE_CACHE_ENABLED=false
```

## Notes

- The GraphQL API URL points to my-cms backend (https://github.com/doitsu2014/my-cms)
- Keycloak authentication uses Authorization Code Flow with PKCE
- Make sure your backend GraphQL server is running before starting the admin_side module
- Keycloak client must be configured with PKCE enabled
